// src/pages/outdoor/smoker-repair/brands/big-green-egg.astro
// Wave 6a — Big Green Egg ceramic kamado brand page (Atlanta GA distributor, founded 1974).
// 7 sizes (Mini, MiniMax, Small, Medium, Large, XL, 2XL). Charcoal/wood only — no electric.
// LIFETIME ceramic warranty for registered owners — we navigate warranty path before paid repair.
// $120 OUTDOOR diagnostic universal (per CLAUDE.md §3, smokers = outdoor tier).
// BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.
// 5 schemas (LocalBusiness + Service + Brand + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList).

import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/smoker-repair/brands/big-green-egg/";

const title = "Big Green Egg Repair LA | Mini to 2XL · Lifetime Ceramic Warranty Navigation · $120 Diagnostic";
const description = `Big Green Egg repair across SoCal. Gasket replacement, dome thermometer, ceramic warranty, hardware. Lifetime ceramic warranty navigation. $120 dx.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why are there so few BGE service calls compared to pellet smokers?",
    a: "Architectural simplicity. A Big Green Egg has no electric components, no motors, no electronics. Charcoal and wood fuel, two manual dampers controlling airflow, a felt gasket sealing the dome to the base, a dome thermometer. That's the entire service surface. Pellet smokers have an auger, a fan, an igniter, a control board, and a probe pair, every one of which is a wear component. A BGE owner who keeps the unit covered and replaces the gasket every 5-7 years should expect 20+ years of service-call-free use. The kamados that do break our service threshold are usually gasket replacement plus a thermometer plus customer-education conversation about damper management.",
  },
  {
    q: "My BGE has a cracked fire ring. Is it worth fixing?",
    a: "Often the answer is: file the lifetime ceramic warranty first, before paying us. Big Green Egg Inc covers ceramic body components under lifetime warranty for registered owners. Fire ring, fire box, dome, base — all covered. We help customers file the claim when we see warranty-eligible damage on the diagnostic. Replacement ceramic ships from BGE at no cost, we install it on a follow-up visit at labor-only billing. If your BGE wasn't registered, the warranty path is closed and we'll quote a paid repair, which on a 2XL fire ring or dome can run $400-800 in parts plus labor. Registration takes 5 minutes online and pays back the first time you need it.",
  },
  {
    q: "How often should I replace the BGE gasket?",
    a: "Year 4-7 is typical replacement. The felt gasket compresses over time from heat cycling and dome closure. When you start seeing smoke leaking around the dome edge during a cook, it's compressed past usefulness. Replacement is straightforward: remove the old felt strip, clean the seating surface, apply the new high-temp felt strip, let it cure for one heat cycle. We do this in 30-45 minutes plus parts. $200-360 typical. Many customers DIY the gasket replacement at year 5-7; it's a reasonable owner-side maintenance task.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's the right size BGE for LA outdoor cooking?",
    a: "Most LA backyards we service have a Large (the most popular size), and our service stock reflects that. The Medium suits couples and small families. The XL and 2XL are entertainer/restaurant sizes; we see those in Calabasas, Pacific Palisades, and a handful of small commercial BBQ operations. The MiniMax is the portable that travels well; tailgaters and beach-cookers often have one. Mini and Small are uncommon in our service calls.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can I leave my Big Green Egg outside in the rain?",
    a: "Yes. The ceramic body is weatherproof and BGE is designed to live outdoors year-round. Rain exposure does not damage the ceramic. Two caveats: keep a vinyl cover on it to protect the metal hardware (hinge, dampers, draft door) from rust and to keep the gasket dry between cooks; and if you live near saltwater (Manhattan Beach, Marina del Rey, Malibu), inspect the metal hardware twice a year for accelerated corrosion and lubricate the hinge plus draft door bolts.",
  },
  {
    q: "BGE thermometer reads 50°F off. Can you fix it?",
    a: "Dome thermometer drift is normal at year 4+ and increases with heat-cycle count. We test against a boiling-water reference (212°F at sea level) and replace if drift exceeds 15°F. Replacement runs $160-240 all-in including the dome thermometer ($40-90 part) plus diagnostic plus 15 minutes labor. Some BGE owners prefer to add a bimetal probe thermometer at the cabinet level for more accurate cabinet temps regardless of the dome thermometer reading; we can install that as well.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. BGE component warranties (ceramic lifetime for registered owners, plus shorter terms on metal hardware) are processed through Big Green Egg Inc's authorized service network. We coordinate the BGE warranty claim and don't charge for parts that the manufacturer is replacing. BHGS #A49573, BBB A+, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.",
  },
];

