  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="Big Green Egg · Ceramic Kamado · Lifetime Ceramic Warranty · LA Same-Day"
  title="Big Green Egg Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle={`Mini through 2XL. Gasket replacement, dome thermometer, hardware service, lifetime ceramic warranty navigation for registered owners. $120 outdoor diagnostic. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Big Green Egg Repair"
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Big Green Egg service</p>
    <h2>The simplest smoker we service, and often the cheapest call you'll have.</h2>

    <p>Big Green Egg is the American ceramic kamado distributor headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia (Big Green Egg Inc, founded 1974). Seven sizes from Mini to 2XL. Charcoal and wood fuel only, no electric components, no electronics. Lifetime warranty on ceramic body components for registered owners. Across our SoCal service territory, BGE is the most common ceramic kamado we touch by a wide margin: most LA backyard outdoor cooks who own ceramic own a Large.</p>

    <p>The honest framing on Big Green Egg service: most calls qualify for warranty navigation rather than paid repair. We route the customer through the BGE lifetime ceramic warranty path before quoting parts when the failure is on the ceramic body. The paid-repair conversation is usually limited to gasket replacement, dome thermometer replacement, and hardware service. That's it. The architectural simplicity of a kamado means there's not much to break.</p>

    <p>We service all 7 sizes across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Mini, MiniMax</strong> (portable). <strong>Small, Medium</strong> (couples and small families). <strong>Large</strong> (most common, what we see most often). <strong>XL, 2XL</strong> (entertainer and small commercial).</p>

    <p>$120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/outdoor/smoker-repair/">smoker repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">What we service on a BGE</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">The full service surface, by component.</h2>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Gasket (felt strip seal)</h3>
    <p>The felt strip that seals the dome to the base. Compresses at year 4-7 from heat cycling. When you start seeing smoke leaking around the dome edge during a cook, it's time. Replacement is straightforward: remove old felt, clean seating surface, apply new high-temp felt strip, let it cure for one heat cycle. $200-360 typical all-in.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Dome thermometer</h3>
    <p>Drift over time, normal at year 4+. We test against a boiling-water reference and replace if drift exceeds 15°F. $160-240 all-in. Some owners add a bimetal probe at cabinet level for more accurate temps regardless of dome reading; we can install that.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Ceramic body (fire ring, fire box, dome, base)</h3>
    <p>Lifetime warranty for registered owners. Cracked fire ring, micro-cracks in the dome, fire box damage, all warranty-covered through Big Green Egg Inc. We file the claim on the customer's behalf when we see warranty-eligible damage on the diagnostic. Replacement ceramic ships from BGE at no cost; we install on follow-up at labor-only billing. If your BGE wasn't registered, the warranty path is closed; paid repair on a 2XL fire ring or dome can run $400-800 in parts plus labor.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Hardware (hinge, draft door, dampers, handle)</h3>
    <p>Draft door bolt seizing is the most common hardware service item. Lubrication usually solves it; replacement bolts are $20-80 each. Hinge spring replacement at year 8+ on heavy-use units. Top damper (the rEGGulator) and bottom damper rarely fail on residential units; lubrication and cleaning resolve most issues. Coastal addresses (Manhattan Beach, Marina del Rey, Malibu) accelerate hardware corrosion; we recommend bi-annual lubrication on those installs.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top BGE repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Gasket replacement (year 4-7).</strong> Smoke leaking around dome edge. $200-360 all-in.</li>
      <li><strong>Dome thermometer drift (year 4+).</strong> Inaccurate temps. $160-240 all-in.</li>
      <li><strong>Ceramic crack diagnosis (warranty path).</strong> Fire ring, fire box, dome. We file BGE warranty claim for registered owners.</li>
      <li><strong>Draft door bolt seizing.</strong> Lubrication (no parts) or bolt replacement ($40-120).</li>
      <li><strong>Hinge spring failure (year 8+).</strong> Dome won't stay open. $180-280 all-in.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal hardware corrosion.</strong> Manhattan Beach, Marina del Rey, Malibu. Lubrication plus selective hardware replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Customer education (damper management, fuel quality).</strong> Sometimes the 'service call' resolves at the diagnostic with a conversation about lump charcoal quality or damper technique.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades, BGE Large (2014 install, year 11)</h3>
        <p>Customer reported smoke leaking around dome. Inspected: gasket compressed and torn in 3 spots after 11 years of use. Replaced felt gasket, verified dome-to-base seal under closed-damper smoke test. While there, inspected fire ring, small crack starting. Filed BGE lifetime ceramic warranty claim on customer's behalf. Replacement fire ring shipped no-charge. Customer paid $120 plus $120 gasket plus 35 minutes labor on the gasket = $300; ceramic was on warranty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood, BGE Medium (2017 install)</h3>
        <p>Customer thought thermometer was 'off'. Tested against boiling water reference: drift was 22°F high. Replaced dome thermometer. Total: $120 plus $80 part plus 15 minutes labor = $200.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach, BGE XL (2019 install)</h3>
        <p>Owner called about gasket plus draft door bolt that wouldn't open. Replaced gasket, freed the seized bolt with penetrating lubricant, replaced one bolt that was past saving. Total: $120 plus $140 parts plus 50 minutes labor = $360.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, BGE 2XL (2010 install, year 15)</h3>
        <p>Customer reported dome cracked at the hinge mount. Year 15, registered owner. Photographed the damage, filed BGE warranty claim. Replacement dome shipped from Atlanta in 14 days. Returned for install: dome swap, gasket reinstall, full reassembly. Total: $120 plus $0 parts (warranty) plus 90 minutes labor on install = $260. Customer's research had assumed $1,500-2,000 paid repair.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for BGE, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>All 7 sizes (Mini, MiniMax, Small, Medium, Large, XL, 2XL)</li>
      <li>Gasket replacement</li>
      <li>Dome thermometer drift recalibration and replacement</li>
      <li>Draft door, hinge, damper hardware service</li>
      <li>Fire ring and fire box ceramic inspection</li>
      <li>BGE lifetime ceramic warranty claim coordination for registered owners</li>
      <li>Customer education (damper management, fuel quality, cleaning)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> ceramic body modifications (drilling, machining, structural changes that void warranty); custom EGG nest or table fabrication; outdoor masonry work to integrate the EGG into a built-in surround. If you call us and we determine the failure is fully covered under BGE's lifetime ceramic warranty, we'll often suggest you contact your BGE dealer directly and skip our visit, because the dealer can sometimes process the claim faster than coordinating through us. Honest answer, not a sales pitch.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BGE repair costs.</h2>
    <p class="lead">$120 outdoor diagnostic, waived with repair. Many BGE calls resolve at warranty navigation rather than paid repair; we don't charge for parts the manufacturer is replacing.</p>
    <table class="price-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical Cost</th></tr></thead>
